        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 1:30PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 129 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Huntsville, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sebastopol, Trinity, Oakhurst, Riverside, Groveton, and Huntsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for southeastern
Texas.</instruction>
